{
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, to manage the context window limitations of LLMs, TestBench [167] and APT [171] propose code reduction strategies.",
    "By leveraging AST analysis to remove the bodies of irrelevant methods while retaining their signatures, these approaches provide the most critical structural information within limited token constraints.",
    "Another study explicitly compares the efficacy of providing full source files versus precise context extracted via static analysis (e.g., signatures of invoked methods, used fields).",
    "The findings reveal that the latter, due to its conciseness and high relevance, enables LLMs to successfully generate tests for a larger number of methods while also being more cost-effective [116].Path Constraint Extraction.",
    "To achieve more systematic testing of complex control flows, researchers have explored various methods to guide LLMs in covering specific program paths."
  ]
}